'<p>A <strong>bill of materials (BOM)</strong> is a comprehensive list of parts, items, assemblies, and sub-assemblies that are required to build, manufacture, or repair a product or machine. It details all the raw materials, components, and instructi'
||'ons necessary for the assembly process.</p>',
'<h3>Normal item included in a BOM:</h3>',
'<ol>',
'<li><strong>Item number</strong>: A unique identifier for each component.</li>',
'<li><strong>Description</strong>: A brief description of the component.</li>',
'<li><strong>Quantity</strong>: The number of units of that component required.</li>',
'<li><strong>Unit of measure</strong>: The unit used to measure the component (e.g., pieces, meters, kilograms).</li>',
'<li><strong>Supplier</strong>: The vendor from whom the component is sourced.</li>',
'<li><strong>Notes</strong>: Additional information or specifications about the component.</li>',
'</ol>',
'<p>In industrial and manufacturing contexts, a BOM is crucial for inventory management, production planning, cost estimation, and ensuring quality and compliance.</p>'))
