'<p><strong>Instructions for Consulting ZB Lists on SMI Machines:</strong></p>',
'<p>In this section, you will find a table containing the ZB codes used in the precompiled lists for SMI machines, along with a search field to facilitate your query.</p>',
'<h3>What is a ZB List?</h3>',
'<p>A ZB List is a group of spare parts that SMI considers crucial for the customer. These lists can be categorized as follows:</p>',
'<ul>',
'<li><strong>First Aid List:</strong> Essential spare parts in case of unexpected failures.</li>',
'<li><strong>Recommended Mechanical Parts List:</strong> Spare parts recommended for routine maintenance.</li>',
'<li><strong>Spare Parts List for Scheduled Maintenance:</strong> Includes all necessary spare parts according to the machine''s maintenance program, from when it is new until it reaches a specified number of operating hours.</li>',
'</ul>',
'<p><strong>Example:</strong> A maintenance list for an EBS machine with 6000 hours includes all the necessary spare parts for maintenance at 1500 hours (4 times), 3000 hours (2 times), and 6000 hours (1 time).</p>',
'<h3>How to Consult a ZB List?</h3>',
'<p>To see the contents of a specific list, click on the "ITEM" column within the table shown below.</p>'))
